node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Can you guess where this was shot in Dubai and would you visit this observation deck? 🇦🇪

📍 Dubai

From scuba diving and snorkeling, to horseback riding on the beach, to browsing art galleries and museums, to indulging in gastronomic feasts, Anguilla will leave you spoiled for choice. It enjoys warm and comfortable temperatures all year round, too—so you can make your travel plans with ease. ☀️

Does Anguilla sound like your ideal kind of destination? 🇦🇮

Check out their adventures with @Robert.wall @faayeded @es_dons in the sun-drenched Turks and Caicos Islands! ☀️

Does this make you miss tropical getaways? Where's your favorite island escape? 🏝

A sunset session with @takemyhearteverywhere in Mykonos taken before the pandemic is currently the setup that we sorely miss. ❤️

Basking in carefree ease, enjoying sunsets with friendly strangers, and bumping elbows with our loved ones are some of the things we miss about our pre-pandemic adventures. Let us all stay steadfast in following safety protocols—so we can get closer to relishing in moments like this again. 🇬🇷

Moreover, as wildfires are aggravated by heat waves all over the world, please educate yourself in today's climate change, do your part, and support green leaders and initiatives. If you can, please donate to @wwf @world_wildlife and other credible organizations leading the climate fight. 🙏🏼

What do you look forward to when we're all able to live and travel more freely again? 💭

📽 @takemyhearteverywhere
📍 Mykonos, Greece
🎶 Sam Smith - Fire On Fire

A Lisbon classic via @mylondonfairytales. 💛 If you happen to be exploring the capital of Portugal, riding or checking out the Elevador da Bica is a must-do. 🚋

Also known as the Bica Funicular, this yellow picturesque ride takes tourists and commuters between the Largo do Calhariz to Rua de São Paulo. With a journey that finishes in less than 5 minutes, it runs every 15 minutes from 7 am to 9 pm on Mondays to Saturdays, and 9 am to 9 pm on Sundays.

Have you been to Lisbon and would you like to experience a ride here? 🇵🇹

📽 @mylondonfairytales 
📍 Elevador da Bica, Lisbon, Portugal
🎶 Peter Bjorn and John - Young Folks

node.text:
We're loving @anamaria's view of the Adriatic Sea in Hvar Island, Croatia's tropical gem that's sought-after by even the most discerning travelers. 🏝

Beyond the glitz and glamour of its main town, Hvar Island features a mild climate, warm winters, and dense Mediterranean nature that makes for a refreshing getaway. From white-washed towns, ancient olive trees and vineyards, charming cobbled streets, and pristine beaches and coves, Hvar Island offers plenty in store for you. ✨

Have you heard of this island and have you ever been to Croatia? 🇭🇷

📽 @anamaria
📍 Hvar Island, Croatia
🎶 will.i.am - Good Morning

Roasting marshmallows @chrisburkard-style. 😎 Do you remember the historic eruption of the Fagradalsfjall volcano this year? 🔥

Earlier this year in March, the Fagradalsfjall volcano located in Iceland’s Reykjanes peninsula, erupted after lying dormant for 800 years. A few months later, it continues spewing lava and recently picked up its intensity again this August.

For those who are curious how it looks like at the moment, you can watch a live stream of the volcano on www.visiticeland.com/eruption. 🇮🇸

📽 @chrisburkard
📍 Fagradalsfjall, Iceland
🎶 Iko Iko (My Bestie) (feat. Small Jam) - Justin Wellington

Hanging out with @matiasderada thanks to @crillon_tours at the world's biggest mirror, a distinctive and surreal salt flat that stretches 4,086 square miles in Bolivia. 🇧🇴

Called the Salar de Uyuni, this otherworldly destination is one of the most unmissable destinations to explore when in South America. When covered with water, it has a superb reflective surface that makes you feel like you're walking on the sky. ✨

Did this make you want to travel with your friends? Tag who you want to bring here! 🙌🏼

📽 @matiasderada
🇧🇴 @crillon_tours 
📍 Salar de Uyuni, Bolivia

node.text:
These endless flower fields shot by @nick_skeyes are currently what we're daydreaming about. When in the Netherlands, you must pay a visit to one of their breathtaking tulip fields. 🌷

The tulip season usually spans from the end of March until mid-May during springtime, but the flowers are usually at their prime halfway through April. Witnessing millions of tulips blooming is truly a spectacle, especially with that colors range from red, pink, white, yellow, and purple. 😍

Does this make you want to plan a trip to the Netherlands? Where do you think are the most beautiful tulip fields in the world? 🇳🇱

📸 @nick_skeyes
📍 Holland, Netherlands

Nature's playground at @visitrasalkhaimah. 🔥 Nestled in the mountains of Ras Al Khaimah lies Wadi Sha'ah, an incredible moderate-to-hard hiking destination that will please experienced hikers and outdoor enthusiasts. 🇦🇪

If you're in for an adrenaline-packed adventure in the UAE, you must make your way to Wadi Sha'ah. Presenting unique hiking challenges, it features boulder hopping, scree slopes, dry waterfalls, donkey trails, and rugged paths. A good level of fitness is required to conquer the 13km full-circuit trail, so planning and preparing for the hike is a must. 👌🏼

Would you take a hike here and have you visited Ras Al Khaimah yet?

📽 @reme_martyr, @tomjauncey, @faisalriazkhan
📍 Wadi Sha'ah, @visitrasalkhaimah, UAE
